race.comment: BOUTIQUE BELLE (13) is on debut for the Grantham stable in the famous cerise and white silks. She was very impressive in her latest trial over 950m and looks poised for a bold run on debut. May need some luck form the barrier, but if the breaks come she'll take plenty of beating. CAPRICIOUS RULER (7) is another debutant who looks a promising type on resumption. Her latest trial coming into this was very nice with Pike hopping in the saddle for her debut. Been given plenty of time to develop and she looks a leading chance based on her latest outing. RISING FAME (3) disappointed on resumption and the stable hit the reset button, going back to the trials and being reproduced here 49 days later. Maps better this time around and can improve sharply. KING OF MUSTER (2) was solid on debut and the form out of that race worked out nicely. Can feature. ALMOST ARTIE (5) can feature first-up.
